net.entersol.iogate
Interface IOResponce

All Known Implementing Classes:
Gdbc
public interface IOResponce

Server response will goes to one of these functions if IOGate class is used to communicate with server then this interface should be implemented and an instant of it passes to the calling function. Then according to the success or failure of the connection onCallBackSuccess or onCallBackFailure will called respectively

onCallBackFailure

void onCallBackFailure(IOGateException ioge)
Called when the service failed to return successfully
This method is called if there is a problem occurred to the service; problems like:
  1. disconnection of network
  2. wrong service call
  3. unauthorized call
  4. problems inside service itself

Parameters:
ioge - is an exception that provided by the connecter class to the caller class to identify problem type
